Membership of the Mediterranean Union proposed by Sarkozy:
According to the latest proposals, Albania , Bosnia and Herzegovina , Croatia , Monaco and Montenegro will also be part of the MU.
such as Germany as it did not approve of EU funds being used in a project which it did not have influence in.

The project is supported by Spain,
. All other EU states would have been silent observers
The original proposals would have only included those EU states who were bordering the Mediterranean: Portugal , Spain, Italy, Malta, Greece and Cyprus.
The idea is to form a "bridge" between Europe , North Africa and the Middle East .
